siers: A New History of Indiana|last=Madison|first=James H.|date=2014|publisher=Indiana University Press|isbn=9780253013088}}</ref>\n<ref name= Mansch>{{Cite book|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=NMt-yrjVE50C}}|title=Abraham Lincoln, President-elect: The Four Critical Months from Election to Inauguration|last=Mansch|first=Larry D.|date=2005|publisher=McFarland|isbn=9780786420261}}</ref>\n<ref name= McGovern>{{Cite book|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=oytingEACAAJ}}|title=Abraham Lincoln: The American Presidents Series: The 16th President, 1861-1865|last=McGovern|first=George S.|authorlink=George McGovern|date=2009|publisher=Henry Holt and Company|isbn=9780805083453}}</ref>\n<ref name= McPherson1992>{{Cite book|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=vFNppNaal6AC}}|title=Abraham Lincoln and the Second American Revolution|last=McPherson|first=James M.|date=June 4, 1992|publisher=Oxford University Press, USA|isbn=9780195076066}}</ref>\n<ref name= McPherson1993>{{Cite book|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=09FkZqu_YcMC}}|title=Battle Cry of Freedom: The Civil War Era|last=McPherson|first=James M.|date=September 29, 2005|publisher=OUP USA|isbn=9780195168952}}</ref>\n<ref name= McPherson2009>{{Cite book|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=3BMSDAAAQBAJ}}|title=Abraham Lincoln|last=McPherson|first=James M.|last2=McPherson|first2=George Henry Davis 86 Professor of American History James M.|date=2009|publisher=Oxford University Press, USA|isbn=9780195374520}}</ref>\n<ref name= Neely1992>{{cite book |authorlink=Mark E. Neely Jr. |last=Neely |first=Mark E. |title=The Fate of Liberty: Abraham Lincoln and Civil Liberties |publisher=Oxford University Press |year=1992 |pages=3\u201331 |url=https://www.questia.com/library/79055660/the-fate-of-liberty-abraham-lincoln-and-civil-liberties |access-date=October 29, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141029142532/https://www.questia.com/library/79055660/the-fate-of-liberty-abraham-lincoln-and-civil-liberties |archive-date=Oct